  "description": "Figure-Eight topology as a pad. The over-under alternating coupling pattern — where every strand crosses two others with opposite-sign coefficients — creates an interference structure denser than the Trefoil ring. At braidDepth=0.71, just above the WEAVE-I threshold, the alternating constructive/destructive interference builds a wide, slightly inharmonic spectral haze. macroKnot=0.45 pulls halfway toward Torus, smoothing out the alternating pattern into something between alternation and symmetric surface coupling. Triangle strands soften the crossings. High reverb fills the space between collisions.",
